# shadcn/ui Component Library

This project uses **shadcn/ui** as the primary UI component library for all interface elements.

## Configuration

The project is configured with shadcn/ui using the **"new-york"** style variant. See [components.json](mdc:components.json) for the complete configuration.

- **Style**: new-york
- **Components path**: `@/components/ui`
- **Utils path**: `@/lib/utils` (see [utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts))
- **Icon library**: Lucide React
- **CSS Variables**: Enabled with neutral base color

## Component Installation

When you need a shadcn/ui component that isn't already installed, use this command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

### Common Components
Examples of frequently used components:
- `npx shadcn@latest add button`
- `npx shadcn@latest add input`
- `npx shadcn@latest add form`
- `npx shadcn@latest add card`
- `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`
- `npx shadcn@latest add toast`
- `npx shadcn@latest add label`
- `npx shadcn@latest add separator`

## Usage Guidelines

1. **Always use shadcn/ui components** for all UI elements instead of creating custom components from scratch
2. **Import components** from `@/components/ui/[component-name]`
3. **Customize components** by modifying the generated files in `src/components/ui/` if needed
4. **Use the cn() utility** from [utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts) for conditional class merging
5. **Follow Tailwind CSS classes** for styling, which are pre-configured to work with shadcn/ui

## Available Components

Check the [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for a complete list of available components.

## Project Integration

- Components are automatically configured to work with the existing [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts)
- CSS variables are defined in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)  
- TypeScript definitions are handled automatically through the shadcn/ui installation